    <briefdescription>
<para>The Gini gain, a measure of set purity usable as a fitness function (FitnessFunction) for decision trees. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>This is the exact same thing as the well-known Gini impurity, but negated<mdash/>since the decision tree will be trying to maximize gain (and the Gini impurity would need to be minimized). </para>
    </detaileddescription>
